# FrankenWM - ~/pkgsrc/wm/frankenwm

First make a copy of config.def.h and do your edits

$ cd ~/pkgsrcwm/frankenwm/
$ make

Once its done, don't run make install ðŸ˜‰

$ cd work
$ mv config.def.h config.def.h.orig 
$ cp /path/to/your/modified/config.def.h ~/pkgsrc/wm/frankenwm/work/
$ cd ..
$ mkpatches
$ make clean

Then run:

$rm patches/patch-config.def.h.orig 

Then add a comment to patch-config.def.h inside the patches directory. Something along the lines of "personal mods" etc.

Then run:
 
$ make makepatchsum      */to generate the sha sum of your patch/*

Now you can do:

$ make 
$ make install
